<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="249" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,759,1218]" pageId="5" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,975,1002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="249">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[339,551,976,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Bubaces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis box="[339,551,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="249">Bubaces castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[606,654,976,1002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="249">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus, is segregated by having the dorsal surface of the pronotum, clavi and coria glabrous, the coria lack the circular yellow to creamy-yellow subapical spots, the head ventrally has a shallow longitudinal sulcus, the rostrum reaches the posterior border of abdominal sternite IV, all tibiae are sparsely spined, and the ostiolar peritremes in male specimens are raised, above the pleural surface, posteriorly with a gentle and open curve, resembling a question mark.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,759,1218]" box="[199,1426,1155,1182]" pageId="5" pageNumber="249">
This species is included in the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[555,665,1156,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Bubaces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis box="[555,665,1156,1181]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="249">castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” group by having the total length of the body longer than 
<quantity box="[1319,1422,1156,1182]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="249" unit="mm" value="4.7">4.70 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
